  exerciseName: OutOfBounds
  exerciseTitle: Handle Out of Bounds
  exerciseText: Edit the function to return -1 if the index is out of bounds instead
    of throwing an error.
  hintText: Check whether the values are > 0 and below the size of that dimension,
    use GetLength(n).
  solutionText: "public int GetValue(int x, int y) {\r\n    if (x < 0 || \r\n       
    y < 0 ||\r\n        x >= int2DArray.GetLength(0) ||\r\n        y >= int2DArray.GetLength(1))
    {\r\n        return -1;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    return int2DArray[x, y];\r\n}"
  completedText: In this exercise you learned to test the bounds of a multidimensional
    array, this is very important to make your code robust and not break if you give
    it an invalid value.
